The paper deals with the classification of skin lesions using convolutional neural networks, which is a common application of computer vision (cs.CV). The use of ResNet-152 architecture and data augmentation techniques also suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging, which could fall under the sub-categories of multimedia (cs.MM) or information retrieval (cs.IR) in the context of medical diagnosis.
